hgroup
  h1 The Grid
  h3 16 columns grid example

p.description
  | Artwork's base grid is a variation of the Skeleton's grid system.
  | The syntax is simple and it's effective cross browser, but the
  | awesome part is that it also has the flexibility to go mobile
  | like a champ. Go ahead, resize the browser and watch as the layout reacts!

.sample
  - (0..11).each do |i|
    div.row
      div class="code column-#{i+1}"
        .inner = "#{i+1}"
      - unless i == 11
        div class="code column-#{12-(i+1)}"
          .inner= "#{11-(i+1)}"

  div.row
    div class="code column column-1"
      .inner 1
    div class="code column column-3"
      .inner 3
    div class="code column column-2"
      .inner 2
    div class="code column column-4"
      .inner 4
    div class="code column column-2"
      .inner 2

  div.row
    div class="text column-4"= lorem.paragraph
    div class="text column-8"= lorem.paragraphs 2
